@node Requirements "MindGuard: System requirements"

MindGuard should run on any Amiga system with Kickstart
V2.04 or higher.

Translator.library and narrator.device are required for
speech but MindGuard will work without them.

It is also required and generally assumed that you have
a mind to guard.

@endnode

@node Tom "MindGuard: Talking Heads?"

TOM BROKAW'S DIRTY LITTLE SECRET

  If you have ever watched the NBC evening news or MSNBC,
  you know that there is something odd about NBC New's
  Uber-Anchor Tom Brokaw.  This is because he is an android.

  Not just your run-of-the-mill android, mind you, but a
  third generation Simulacrum, specially designed by the
  Disney-Front Imagineers for their Liberati Masters.
  These Simulacrums come in many different models and lines
  that are used for different purposes.  They were first
  developed in the fifties by Walt Disney, under the guise
  of his audio-animatronic research.  The technology has
  matured greatly since then, and simulacrums have gone on
  to infiltrated many aspects of our lives.

  The "man" you are used to seeing anchoring the Nightly
  News on NBC is actually a whole line of Simulacrums, each
  called a Tom Brokaw Unit (TBU).  TBUs were designed for
  propaganda dissemination.  They contain a slew of
  psychotronic, psioptic, and hypnosonic devices that are
  used to make people watching NBC believe what the Liberati
