  most effective psi-gear.  

  The current TBU models have the following features:

    · MS Windows AE: This is the special android version of
      Microsoft's Windows operating system.  (Bill Gates, I
      should point out, isn't actually an android, as one
      would guess, but a Human-Reptilian hybrid who subsists
      mainly on small rodents.)

    · Voice Modulation Sonoglyph: TBU's have the ability to
      encode psycho-suggestive messages in the modulation of
      their voice.  Because of this, TBUs tend to have an
      odd inflection.  Make sure to @{"DePsych" link Depsych} after listening
      to a TBU for a prolonged time.

    · Physio-rhythmic Somnia Inducer:  This feature allows
      TBUs to lull their audiences into a trance state
      through subtle body movements.  These tend to manifest
      themselves in abnormal neck flexes and limp-
      wristedness, but the most dangerous are the blink
      rhythms and eye gyrations.  You should never look a
      TBU directly in the eyes!

  TBUs are not, of course, the only Simulacrums in TV news.
  At NBC, android models include the Stone Philips, Katie
  Couric, Matt Lauer, and Tim Russard varieties.  Peter
  Jennings, Sam Donaldson, and Ted Kopple are notable ABC
  Simulacrums.  (Diane Sawyer, however, is fully biological.
  She, along with Anne Curry from NBC's Today Show, is a
