  And then there is CBS...

WHAT'S THE FREQUENCY KENNETH? 12.62 PHz.

  The truth about Dan Rather almost slipped when a man
  burst into the studio one day while his show was airing
  and screamed out "What's the frequency Kenneth?" before
  being removed by CBS's elite counter-insurgence squad.
  The incident was brushed aside by CBS officials by
  claiming the man was a kook, and later was made completely
  innocuous by the pop-group REM in their mind-numbing song
  ingeniously entitled "What's the Frequency Kenneth?".  But
  just who is Kenneth?  And what is the frequency the man
  referred to?  The answer to these questions are key to
  understanding why CBS's logo is a giant eye.

  Kenneth is Kenneth Steinberg, Dan Rather's operator. Dan
  Rather, like Tom Brokaw, is an android.  But, unlike the
  TBU Simulacrums, Rather is a non-automaton.  In a word
