@node PGP "MindGuard: PGP Signature"

The MindGuard archive has been signed using PGP for your
protection.  To use this security feature, you will need PGP
installed on your Amiga.

To check if the signature matches the archive, type:

   pgp MindGuardxxx.lha.sig MindGuardxxx.lha

(replacing xxx with the version number.)

PGP will warn you if the signature doesn't belong to the file
or if it is not from me.

Below is my (Lyle Zapato) signed public key.  Add it to your
keyring by typing:

   pgp MindGuard.guide

NOTE: Only do this if you received this file from a secure and
      trusted source otherwise this would be a pointlessly
      unsecure act!

